The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Kannur, Dec. 4 (PTI): Nine primary school children were killed when a van ran over them near Kannur in Kerala today, police said. The students were on their way home.           
	The dead are aged between five and eight. The driver, now in custody, said he lost control when a child ran to the middle of the road to pick up his slippers.                   
	 New Delhi: N.D. Tiwari, asked by Delhi High Court to appear before it on December 16 in a paternity suit, has cited his constitutional position as governor to avoid doing so. The appellant, who is the governor of Andhra Pradesh, a constitutional appointee, ought to have been exempted..., his plea said. It will be heard tomorrow. The case has been filed by Rohit Shekhar, who has demanded that Tiwari accept him as his son or take a DNA test.                   
	 New Delhi: Deepak Sandhu, the governments principal information officer, will be the Prime Ministers new media adviser. The 1971 Indian Information Service official, who replaces Sanjaya Baru, will assume office next Wednesday.                  
	 New Delhi: The Delhi government will soon introduce a policy under which it will buy heritage buildings from disinterested private owners, lieutenant governor Tejinder Khanna said. The policy, to be framed by the Delhi government and the Union urban development ministry, is aimed at saving buildings that may fall into ruin, sources said.                                                                                                                         
